Package: rpki
Title: Tools to PKI-enable Utilities in R and Allow for Secure Connections and Package Installation
Version: 1.0.5
Authors@R: c(
    person("Joshua", "Bradley", , "jgbradley1@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("nbgallery", role = "cph")
    )
Description: A collection of wrapper functions that configure the 'httr' package and other base R functions for
    PKI-authenticated services. Conceptually similar to the Python 'pypki2' and `ipydeps`
    packages, this package uses the same mypki configuration file.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
Depends:
    R (>= 3.3.0),
    httr (>= 1.2.1)
Imports:
    openssl (>= 1.4.1),
    getPass (>= 0.1-1),
    jsonlite (>= 1.3),
    stringr (>= 1.2.0)
Suggests: testthat (>= 1.0.2)
URL: https://github.com/nbgallery/rpki, https://github.com/nbgallery
